{
  "deckTitle": "Agents 101 — Offline Study Notes Demo",
  "lanes": [
    {
      "title": "Main",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "Agents 101",
          "status": "done",
          "slides": [
            {
              "title": "What is an Agent?",
              "bg": "#0f172a",
              "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 60%, #0b1220 100%)",
              "color": "#e2e8f0",
              "accent": "#3b82f6",
              "padding": "48px 72px",
              "align": "left",
              "verticalAlign": "center",
              "duration": 60,
              "blocks": [
                { "type": "badge", "text": "FOUNDATIONS", "icon": "Layers", "bg": "rgba(59,130,246,0.18)", "color": "#93c5fd" },
                { "type": "spacer", "h": 10 },
                { "type": "heading", "text": "Agents Close the Loop", "size": "3xl", "weight": 700, "color": "#f8fafc" },
                { "type": "text", "text": "Unlike a single-shot prompt, an agent plans, acts, observes, and revises — each step is auditable.", "size": "lg", "color": "#cbd5e1" },
                { "type": "spacer", "h": 8 },
                { "type": "flow", "items": [
                  { "icon": "Brain", "label": "Plan", "sublabel": "What to try" },
                  { "icon": "Play", "label": "Act", "sublabel": "Call a tool" },
                  { "icon": "Eye", "label": "Observe", "sublabel": "Read result" },
                  { "icon": "RefreshCw", "label": "Revise", "sublabel": "Update plan" }
                ], "arrowColor": "#3b82f6", "loop": true, "loopLabel": "until goal reached", "loopColor": "#64748b", "loopStyle": "dashed" }
              ],
              "studyNotes": {
                "text": "An **agent** is a goal-driven loop: plan → act → observe → revise. This is different from a single-shot LLM call in one critical way — each iteration is an auditable step you can inspect, debug, and roll back.\n\nThe loop matters because *reasoning becomes visible*. When an agent picks a tool, you can log the choice. When it reads a result, you can verify the read. When it revises the plan, you can compare before/after. This makes agent behavior debuggable in a way that monolithic LLM outputs are not.\n\nFor the original formulation of this pattern, see the [ReAct paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.03629). For a broader overview of what an [agent](#agent) really is versus a [tool](#tool)-calling chatbot, read the inline X-Ray terms on this page.",
                "diagram": "<svg viewBox='0 0 320 120' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'><defs><marker id='a' markerWidth='8' markerHeight='8' refX='6' refY='4' orient='auto'><path d='M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 z' fill='#3b82f6'/></marker></defs><rect x='10' y='40' width='60' height='40' rx='6' fill='#1e293b' stroke='#3b82f6'/><text x='40' y='64' text-anchor='middle' font-size='11' fill='#e2e8f0' font-family='monospace'>Plan</text><rect x='90' y='40' width='60' height='40' rx='6' fill='#1e293b' stroke='#3b82f6'/><text x='120' y='64' text-anchor='middle' font-size='11' fill='#e2e8f0' font-family='monospace'>Act</text><rect x='170' y='40' width='60' height='40' rx='6' fill='#1e293b' stroke='#3b82f6'/><text x='200' y='64' text-anchor='middle' font-size='11' fill='#e2e8f0' font-family='monospace'>Observe</text><rect x='250' y='40' width='60' height='40' rx='6' fill='#1e293b' stroke='#3b82f6'/><text x='280' y='64' text-anchor='middle' font-size='11' fill='#e2e8f0' font-family='monospace'>Revise</text><line x1='70' y1='60' x2='88' y2='60' stroke='#3b82f6' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#a)'/><line x1='150' y1='60' x2='168' y2='60' stroke='#3b82f6' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#a)'/><line x1='230' y1='60' x2='248' y2='60' stroke='#3b82f6' stroke-width='1.5' marker-end='url(#a)'/><path d='M 280 80 Q 280 105 40 105 Q 40 95 40 80' stroke='#64748b' stroke-width='1.5' stroke-dasharray='4 3' fill='none' marker-end='url(#a)'/><text x='160' y='115' text-anchor='middle' font-size='9' fill='#94a3b8' font-family='monospace'>loop until goal reached</text></svg>",
                "questions": [
                  "Why does exposing the loop matter for debugging and trust?",
                  "When would you stop iterating — cost, confidence, or task completion?",
                  "How do agents fail differently from single-shot prompts?"
                ],
                "glossary": {
                  "agent": {
                    "definition": "A goal-driven loop that plans, acts, observes, and revises — not a single-shot prompt. Each iteration is an auditable step.",
                    "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intelligent_agent"
                  },
                  "tool": {
                    "definition": "An external capability an agent can call — a function, API, or command — whose result feeds back into the next planning step."
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "No Study Notes Here",
              "bg": "#0f172a",
              "color": "#e2e8f0",
              "accent": "#3b82f6",
              "padding": "48px 72px",
              "align": "center",
              "verticalAlign": "center",
              "duration": 30,
              "blocks": [
                { "type": "heading", "text": "This slide has no studyNotes", "size": "2xl", "color": "#f8fafc" },
                { "type": "text", "text": "The live Vera Teacher panel will generate content on demand when you open student mode.", "size": "md", "color": "#94a3b8" }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
